This paper deals with the study of algebraic ordinary differential equations (AODEs) and their solutions. The paper presents a sufficient condition for an AODE to have a degree bound for its polynomial solutions, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the recognition of poles of rational solutions from their coefficients, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and dynamical systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper presents an algorithm for determining rational solutions of certain AODEs, which falls under the category of scientific computing (cs.SC) and optimization (cs.LO).
